*Jiutian Chemical Group (JIUC SP) 3Q20 results*- Reported a new quarterly record 3Q20 net profit of Rmb51.9m (+2038% yoy; +59% qoq)  which came on the back of greater operating leverage. The good set of results overshot our 3Q20 earnings estimate of Rmb38.8m  due mainly to higher-than-expected DMF ASP of Rmb6 195/tonne (+36.4% yoy; +37.3% qoq).- Revenue gained 8.8% yoy to Rmb267.0m (-3.4% qoq) due to higher DMF ASP of Rmb6 195/tonne (+36.4% yoy; +37.3% qoq)  but slipped sequentially from lower utilisation rate of 44% (3Q19: 49%; 2Q20: 56%) for its DMF plant due to a scheduled maintenance shutdown of 20 days in Sep 20 as expected.- Accordingly  3Q20 gross margin spiked to 31.4% (3Q19: 7.7%; 2Q20: 19.4%) from: 1) higher product prices  as well as a 2) lower cost for methanol  a major raw material for DMF.- While spot DMF prices is seeing some softening since our initiation  prices are expected to stay elevated on sustainable demand  driven by strong growth in both the local and export markets for their end-products  as well as a rising demand from users in the lithium batteries and semiconductor sectors.- We have lifted our 2021F DMF ASP assumption slightly by 2.9% to Rmb7 200/tonne  keeping a healthy buffer of 30% below the current spot price of Rmb9 350/tonne.- Maintain BUY with a higher TP of S$0.18  pegged to 5x 2021F PE  or -1SD of its historical 13-year average. Jiutian currently trades at 3.2x 2021F PE.
